{"lemma":"أَفْعَيَيْنِ","slug":"أَفْعَيَيْنِ","root":"ف.ع.#","root_slug":"ف-ع-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ع-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34222","n34226"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"viper (venomous snake in the family Viperidae)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"snake (common name of reptiles), serpent","tags":["proscribed"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʔapʕaw- (“viper, a kind of serpent”)."},"ipa":["/ʔaf.ʕan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34222","headword_ar":"افعى","root":"fEw or fEY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became possessed of"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"characterized by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil after good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n34226","headword_ar":"اَفْعًى","root":"fEw or fEY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K) of the fem. gender, but with tenween, (S, Msb,) because it is a subst., not an epithet; (Msb;) [said in the S and Msb to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowFY","text_ar":"اَرْوًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is a mistake, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArwY","text_ar":"اروى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is without tenween;] or it is an epithet and a subst.; (K, TA;) but mostly a subst.; (TA;) [if used as an epithet, it is without tenween, written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEaY","text_ar":"اَفْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", being also of the measure of a verb;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain serpent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a malignant kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"viper;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufoEuw~N","text_ar":"اُفْعُوٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AufoEuwAn","text_ar":"اُفْعُوان"},{"kind":"text","text":", which see in what follows,]) occurring in a trad., in which it is said that there is no harm in the killing of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufoEuw~","text_ar":"اُفْعُوّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huduw~","text_ar":"حُدُوّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHorim","text_ar":"مُحْرِم"},{"kind":"text","text":", the [final] alif being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in both of these words in the dial. of El-Hijáz: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is spotted, black and white; slender in the neck; broad in the head; it is said that it will not quit its place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"always coiling itself round; and neither antidote nor charm is of any avail against it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes it has two horns"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. it sometimes signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cerastes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horned viper"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufofuwaAnN","text_ar":"اُفْفُوَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xi$aA$N","text_ar":"خِشَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afaAEK","text_ar":"اَفَاعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K. * [In the K, the pl. is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afaAEiY","text_ar":"اَفَاعِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, when indeterminate, is wrong.]) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] by way of comparison [to vipers], (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^afaAEiY","text_ar":"الاَفَاعِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain veins"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwq","text_ar":"عُرُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that branch off from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlibaAni","text_ar":"حَالِبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}